## Gotchas

- {{MIGRATION_GOTCHA_1}}
<!-- Example: "NEVER edit a migration file that has been applied — create a new one instead" -->
- {{MIGRATION_GOTCHA_2}}
<!-- Example: "Adding a NOT NULL column without a default will fail on non-empty tables — always add default or make nullable first" -->
- {{MIGRATION_GOTCHA_3}}
<!-- Example: "Renaming a column is destructive — do expand-contract: add new column → backfill → update code → drop old column" -->
- {{MIGRATION_GOTCHA_4}}
<!-- Example: "Production migrations run during deploy with zero downtime — avoid locking statements (full table rewrites, exclusive locks)" -->

## When NOT to Use This Skill

- Seeding data — use `{{CMD_SEED}}` instead
- Changing application code without schema changes — no migration needed
- Emergency schema changes on prod without staging validation — escalate to DBA
